- REQ-01 precedes broad global documentation expansion.
- REQ-02 precedes official Documentation release claims.
- REQ-03 precedes BBA production-like claims.
- REQ-04 precedes Lottery randomness/prize/payout design work.
- REQ-05 precedes any DEX read-only UI implementation.
- REQ-06 precedes provider/payout/accounting work.
- REQ-07 through REQ-11 must remain non-executing and should not bypass recovery priorities.
- REQ-12 through REQ-15 are HOLD/backlog control and should not become implementation sprints.

## HOLD Policy

HOLD nuclei are ACS, Governance, and Trading.

Allowed HOLD work:

- backlog control;
- gap/risk documentation;
- contract/interface inventory;
- validation maintenance notes;
- dependency maps.

Forbidden HOLD work:

- runtime mutation;
- API transport implementation;
- live trading;
- real credentials;
- treasury movement;
- on-chain writes;
- production DB;
- executor activation.

## Recovery Policy

Recovery priority is:

1. Global Docs / Instructions.
2. Documentation.
3. BBA-Agency.
4. Lottery as controlled recovery.

Exit criteria must include file ownership, missing-doc repair, validation checklist, and production-disabled language.

## Advancement Policy

L3/L4 advancement is limited to:

- read-only visibility maps;
- contract documentation;
- API/read-model documentation;
- validation plans;
- blocker maps;
- mock/local exit criteria.

Advancement does not authorize production runtime or execution.

